pertubis installation description

You can build pertubis manual via cmake or using the ebuild we provide here
Below you see the packages you need to build and run pertubis.

    * gentoo linux
    * >=sys-apps/paludis-0.24.2
    * >=dev-libs/pcre++
    * >=x11-libs/qt-4.3
    * >=dev-util/cmake-2.4.6-r1

install via ebuild:

    svn co svn://svn.berlios.de/pertubis/trunk/overlay/sys-apps/

    <mv or move the pertubis directory to your portage overlay>

    paludis -i pertubis

install manually:

getting a tarball:

    wget ftp://ftp.berlios.de/pub/pertubis/pertubis-<VERSION>.tar.bz2

unpack the tarball

    tar -xvjpf pertubis-<VERSION>.tar.bz2
    cd pertubis

configuration

    mkdir build
    cd build
    export CXXFLAGS="-march=<YOUR CPU> -O2 -pipe"
    cmake ..

compilation

    make

installation

    make install

Build options

    * Consider using ccmake in place of cmake. Then you get a curses based
      configuration menu for fine tuning
    * you could both build pertubis using a out-of-source or a in-source build process.
      Choose the one you prefer. The ebuild takes the in-source approach - I prefer the
      other one for development.
